title: For Sale:  Ruger Blackhawk - Flattop 44 Magnum - 7 1/2" Barrel - All Original
location: Palm Coast, FL, Florida, United States
postcontent:
Ruger Blackhawk Flattop in 44 Magnum with a 7 1/2" barrel.  They only made 750 of these with this barrel length (confirmed in the blue book of gun values).  This is one of the most collectible Rugers out there.  

Here is a quote from a gunblast article:

"The 7-1/2” and 10” barrel lengths were also introduced in 1959 as part of the Type 4 production.  The April 10, 1959 Distributor price sheet lists the 6-1/2” and 7-1/2” suggested retail price as $96.00 and the 10” as $106.00  Production number estimates of the 7-1/2” and 10” barrel guns vary.  It is generally believed that between 1,000 to 1,500 guns with 10” barrels were made.  The 7-1/2” barrel estimates seem to vary quite widely.  Estimates of 750 to 2,750 believed produced have been given by different sources.  For what it is worth, my personal observation of 7-1/2” versus 10” barreled .44 Flattops over the years tends to support a lower or middle of the road estimate.  When thinking of the ones that I have handled, seen, and/or heard of, it supports that there were fewer, or at least no more, 7-1/2” Flattops made than the 10” guns.  No matter what the estimates, both of these longer barrel .44 “Flattops” are rare!  They are some the most desirable and sought after guns by collectors today."

You can read the whole article here: http://www.gunblast.com/Hamm_44-Flattop.htm 

I also posted this on the Ruger Collectors Association forum which you can see here: http://www.rugercollectorsassociation.com/forums/viewtopic.php?f=4&t=6564&e=0 

I do not have the original box or paperwork.  Everything else is original.  Original grips, sights, finish & trigger/hammer mechanism (has not had the Ruger safety upgrade).  

There is some holster wear at the muzzle and on the cylinder.  There is wear on the cylinder where the sight adjustment screw was down all the way.  There is also a small chip in the bottom of the frame by the grip.  I can only post three pictures with this listing.  I can send more pictures upon request.

This gun functions perfectly and is very, very accurate.

Asking $1400.  All reasonable offers will be considered. 

Buyer pays actual shipping cost and any FFL charges.  Buyer is responsible for knowing if he/she is legally allowed to own this firearm.
